<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hardy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the name of the President and people of the United States, you will
                            make to the President of the Confederation a very warm acknowledgment of
                            the message of brotherly sympathy and sorrow which his excellency sends
                            on behalf of the Federal Council through Mr. Lardy.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>